 \n  Tip: When debugging locally, add `--stacktrace` for better error output.\n  \n  ### End-to-end testing before the commit\n  ```console\n  ./gradlew testAllInfra --stacktrace\n  ```\n  \n  To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\n  ```console\n  GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew testAllInfra --stacktrace\n  ```\n  \n  ### Style and formatting\n  \n  1. To check style use\n      ```console\n      ./gradlew checkstyle\n     ```\n     This will run Checkstyle using `gradle/checkstyle.xml`.\n  \n  2. Spotless Verifies formatting (used in release workflow prior to packaging):\n      ```console\n     ./gradlew spotlessCheck\n      ```\n  3. Auto-fix license headers and formatting locally:\n      ```console\n      ./gradlew spotlessApply\n      ```\n     Spotless enforces the CC0 license header on Java, Groovy, Gradle build scripts, and shell scripts. The metadata/** directory is excluded from header checks.\n  \n  ### Testing one library locally\n  \n  For a single coordinate, CI runs three steps in this order:\n  1. Pull Docker images:\n      ```console\n     ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\n      ```\n  2. Validate index.json file integrity and schemas:\n      ```console\n     ./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\n      ```\n  2. Validate metadata:\n      ```console\n     ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\n      ```\n  3. Then run tests:\n      ```console\n     ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\n     ```\n  \n  To run the same coordinate with future defaults enabled:\n  ```console\n  GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\n  ```\n  \n  ### Testing libraries in bulk\n  \n  To exercise many tests at once, you can target all coordinates or a slice of the test space via the N/M shard syntax.\n  \n  All coordinates:\n  1. Test the whole repo:\n      ```console\n\n=== human-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-49-54-393776Z.log ===\n================================================================================\nTimestamp: 2026-04-28T20:49:54.394026+00:00\nSession: ../../../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge5-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-2448-e88b971f--/2026-04-28T20-48-38-035Z_019dd5d9-dc93-7227-b3c5-d4844c94dce0.jsonl\nEvent Trace:\n[send] prompt\n  Role: You are an expert JVM test engineer specializing in high-coverage integration testing for external libraries.\n  \n  Task:\n  Improve test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2`.\n  \n  Source Context:\n  Coordinate: io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\n  Repository URL: https://github.com/micrometer-metrics/micrometer\n  Main sources:\n  - URL: https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/io/micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/micrometer-core-1.8.2-sources.jar\n  - Local path: local_repositories/source_context/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/main\n  - Files available: 266\n  \n  Active class:\n  - Class: io.micrometer.core.instrument.binder.system.FileDescriptorMetrics\n  - Source file: /home/vjovanov/c/forge5/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/main/extracted/io/micrometer/core/instrument/binder/system/FileDescriptorMetrics.java\n  \n  Progress since the previous dynamic-access report:\n  - Attempts used for this class so far: 0\n  - Newly covered call sites: none\n  - Remaining uncovered call sites after the last report: 3\n  \n  Remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites for this class:\n  - [reflection] java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String) <- io.micrometer.core.instrument.binder.system.FileDescriptorMetrics.getFirstClassFound(FileDescriptorMetrics.java:135) (line 135)\n  - [reflection] java.lang.Class#getDeclaredMe