": \\\"java.security.interfaces.XECKey\\\",\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:193:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.ECPrivateKey\\\"\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:199:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.ECPublicKey\\\"\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:205:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPrivateKey\\\"\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-orgjson/0.11.5/reachability-metadata.json:211:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey\\\"\\ntests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna/5.8.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/test/proxy-config.json:3:    \\\"interfaces\\\": [\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:8:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's public interfaces, fluent builders, and supporting types for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.\\\",\\nmetadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/index.json:23:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"JJWT provides APIs for creating, parsing, and verifying JSON Web Tokens and JSON Web Keys in Java and Android applications. The `jjwt-api` artifact exposes the library's stable public interfaces and fluent builders for JOSE-compliant JWT processing.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.jboss.spec.javax.servlet/jboss-servlet-api_4.0_spec/index.json:16:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Provides the Jakarta Servlet 4.0 specification API as a JBoss-packaged artifact for Java web applications. It defines the standard server-side interfaces for handling HTTP requests, responses, and related web container interactions.\\\"\\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:4967:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPrivateKey\\\"\\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.5.0/reachability-metadata.json:4973:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey\\\"\\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.2.1/reachability-metadata.json:7161:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPrivateKey\\\"\\nmetadata/com.hazelcast/hazelcast/5.2.1/reachability-metadata.json:7167:      \\\"type\\\": \\\"java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey\\\"\\nmetadata/org.apache.activemq/artemis-log-annotation-processor/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"ActiveMQ Artemis Log Annotation Processor is a Java annotation processor for Artemis logging annotations such as LogBundle, Message, LogMessage, and GetLogger. It generates SLF4J-backed implementation classes at compile time and validates message identifiers and placeholders for annotated logging interfaces.\\\",\\nmetadata/xmlpull/xmlpull/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"XML Pull Parsing API defines a small Java API for streaming XML pull parsers and serializers. It supplies interfaces and factory classes that parser implementations use so applications can read and write XML through a common pull-based contract.\\\",\\nmetadata/io.r2dbc/r2dbc-spi/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"R2DBC SPI defines the service provider interfaces and core contracts for reactive relational database connectivity on the JVM. It lets database driver vendors expose non-blocking, Reactive Streams-based access to SQL databases while giving clients a common API to discover connections, execute statements, and consume results.\\\",\\nmetadata/library-and-framework-list.json:1886:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"RESTHeart Commons - Common utilities and interfaces for RESTHeart modules\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.jms/jakarta.jms-api/index.json:10:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Jakarta Messaging API defines interfaces for creating, sending, receiving, and reading messages between Java applications and messaging providers. It standardizes loosely coupled asynchronous communication semantics without providing a concrete messaging implementation.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.immutables/value/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Immutables Value provides compile-time annotations and an annotation processor that generate consistent immutable value objects from abstract classes, interfaces, or annotations. It helps Java projects define type-safe, fluent value types with less handwritten boilerplate.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.glassfish.jaxb/txw2/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"TXW2 is a typed XML writer library that lets Java code generate XML documents through annotated writer interfaces. It provides runtime support for building structured XML output with SAX, StAX, DOM, and stream-based serializers.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.hamcrest/hamcrest-core/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Hamcrest Core provides the stable core API for the Hamcrest matcher framework, including matcher interfaces, assertion helpers, and common matcher implementations. It lets testing tools and applications build composable, readable assertions that express expected conditions in tests.\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.servlet/jakarta.servlet-api/index.json:8:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Jakarta Servlet defines the standard server-side API for Java web applications to process HTTP requests and generate responses. It provides interfaces and classes for servlets, filters, listeners, sessions, and deployment descriptors for Servlet 4.0 applications.\\\",\\nmetadata/jakarta.servlet/jakarta.servlet-api/index.json:23:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Jakarta Servlet defines the standard server-side API for Java web applications to process HTTP requests and generate responses. It provides interfaces and classes for servlets, filters, listeners, sessions, and deployment descriptors in Jakarta EE 9.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.core/index.json:10:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"This artifact provides the core OSGi Service Platform Release 4.3 interfaces and classes. It defines the Framework APIs for bundles, lifecycle management, module wiring, and services used when compiling OSGi-based applications.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.apache.openejb/javaee-api/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"This artifact bundles the Java EE 5 API classes used by Apache OpenEJB into a single jar. It provides the standard javax.* interfaces and annotations needed to compile Java EE applications.\\\",\\nmetadata/net.java.dev.jna/jna/index.json:12:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"JNA provides Java programs with easy access to native shared libraries without requiring JNI code. It lets Java code call native functions and map native data structures through Java interfaces and classes.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.osgi/org.osgi.resource/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"org.osgi.resource provides the OSGi Resource API, a set of interfaces for describing resources, their capabilities, requirements, wires, and wirings. It is used by OSGi frameworks and related services to model dependency resolution and the resolved wiring state of bundles or repository resources.\\\",\\nmetadata/org.apache.maven.surefire/surefire-logger-api/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Surefire Logger API provides dependency-free logging interfaces and utility classes used internally by Apache Maven Surefire components. It centralizes console logging levels, decorators, null logging, and print-stream-backed logging for Surefire and Failsafe runtime code.\\\",\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777408920548}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-04-28T20-45-13-777820Z.log:3119:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_Ek9S71qDtiVJQNdLgUhlizde|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11b97e95c81979f23fee1be27a0ca\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"tests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-server/12.0.1/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/test/reflect-config.json\\ntests/src/org.eclipse.jetty/jetty-server/11.0.12/src/test/r