UbjZNjHbE-In5bfzBwdTaPYHMLWH46yF3NVmltx4TxVoZEt2v2HFizA-k7dy2PgBekhhSFc7mFkjMwUNk3CjXGkr8nbV3MmXV3O2OcYaqvokZJ1WZ5wOl5q54YMvK4_PCXBYg-1rohD5bZMQckSRHZbhXG025zaKZ3dc3faOkwCUKpxLOAefld_qbSpI1vF3-Q1DIUikJXt49B-O9M4OZQVapo0vKGhPFhPHhpBNElUPgHgmZ6Hb1cI68vboPdpTeU6zLtqqOPe53gCFyRpSh_t2X0vPrkuFCOYuTNblkWXZmSFi4g-Ju1kbEl3zO\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Resolving classloader issues**\\\\n\\\\nI need to execute the HazelcastIMapAdapter in isolated classloaders for both Hazelcast3 and Hazelcast5, but it looks like a dependency conflict is blocking both artifact versions. Maybe I can use test fixture classes to fill in the gaps for any missing primary packages while the Hazelcast3 dependency is still around. I really need class availability at runtime in the same classloader to make this work smoothly. Let’s see how to resolve this!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering Java ClassLoader setup**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about placing Java source under `src/testPrimary/java`, with a custom Gradle sourceSet that doesn't interfere with test runtime. Maybe compiling it separately and loading with URLClassLoader in the test is a good route? I wonder if that's too broad. \\\\n\\\\nThe test can utilize URLs for necessary components like the micrometer-core jar and test fixture outputs. It seems I need a child-first ClassLoader for certain dependencies, but that might introduce complexities like using reflection or method handles for dynamic class access.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating classloader and testing options**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering executing library class bytecode, possibly something like TrackDynamicAccess records. I'm worried that direct reflection in tests might be disallowed, but accessing the public API from a child classloader could be a workaround due to testing classloader isolation. However, that feels risky. \\\\n\\\\nPerhaps a separate sourceSet and a JUnit test that forks a new Java process with a different classpath would be more straightforward. But, hmm, tests under a native image shouldn't spawn a Java process, right? That's not ideal.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing class usage**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether I need to include all primary classes. I see that the existing Hazelcast3's LocalMapStats and NearCacheStats are still relevant. The current tests are importing com.hazelcast.core.IMap and creating an old IMap proxy. However, I notice that the HazelcastIMapAdapter CLASS_I_MAP is now the primary fixture for com.hazelcast.map.IMap. I just need to figure out the best way to proceed with this setup!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_anMgAp6vDGj2JeYfYVcxh0aX|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11cb141e08197b76f847dae08376d\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short && git log --oneline -3\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 46493, \"output\": 3092, \"cacheRead\": 4608, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 54193, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777409154122, \"responseId\": \"resp_07970394a73d0df90169f11c8361288197a191ea44a4c4bff2\"}}\n5594:  8a2380566d (HEAD -> ai/add-lib-support-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2) Add Micrometer Hazelcast IMap adapter coverage\n5599:  8a2380566d (HEAD -> ai/add-lib-support-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2) Add Micrometer Hazelcast IMap adapter coverage\n5602:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_anMgAp6vDGj2JeYfYVcxh0aX|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11cb141e08197b76f847dae08376d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/\\n8a2380566d (HEAD -> ai/add-lib-support-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2) Add Micrometer Hazelcast IMap adapter coverage\\n7a17c84176 Scaffold io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\\nd54619f2a4 (origin/master, origin/HEAD, master) [GenAI] Add support for org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-component-annotations:1.5.4 using gpt-5.5 (#2580)\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777409201946}}\n5603:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_anMgAp6vDGj2JeYfYVcxh0aX|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11cb141e08197b76f847dae08376d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/\\n8a2380566d (HEAD -> ai/add-lib-support-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2) Add Micrometer Hazelcast IMap adapter coverage\\n7a17c84176 Scaffold io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.8.2\\nd54619f2a4 (origin/master, origin/HEAD, master) [GenAI] Add support for org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-component-annotations:1.5.4 using gpt-5.5 (#2580)\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777409201946}}\n5604:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Resolving classloader issues**\\n\\nI need to execute the HazelcastIMapAdapter in isolated classloaders for both Hazelcast3 and Hazelcast5, but it looks like a dependency conflict is blocking both artifact versions. Maybe I can use test fixture classes to fill in the gaps for any missing primary packages while the Hazelcast3 dependency is still around. I really need class availability at runtime in the same classloader to make this work smoothly. Let’s see how to resolve this!\\n\\n**Considering Java ClassLoader setup**\\n\\nI'm thinking about placing Java source under `src/testPrimary/java`, with a custom Gradle sourceSet that doesn't interfere with test runtime. Maybe compiling it separately and loading with URLClassLoader in the test is a good route? I wonder if that's too broad. \\n\\nThe test can utilize URLs for necessary components like the micrometer-core jar and test fixture outputs. It seems I need a child-first ClassLoader for certain dependencies, but that might introduce complexities like using reflection or method handles for dynamic class access.\\n\\n**Evaluating classloader and testing options**\\n\\nI'm considering executing library class bytecode, possibly something like TrackDynamicAccess records. I'm worried that direct reflection in tests might be disallowed, but accessing the public API from a child classloader could be a workaround due to testing classloader isolation. However, that feels risky. \\n\\nPerhaps a separate sourceSet and a JUnit test that forks a new Java process with a different classpath would be more straightforward. But, hmm, tests under a native image shouldn't spawn a Java process, right? That's not ideal.\\n\\n**Analyzing class usage**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to include all primary classes. I see that the existing Hazelcast3's LocalMapStats and NearCacheStats are still relevant. The current tests are importing com.hazelcast.core.IMap and creating an old IMap proxy. However, I notice that the HazelcastIMapAdapter CLASS_I_MAP is now the primary fixture for com.hazelcast.map.IMap. I just need to figure out the best way to proceed with this setup!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_07970394a73d0df90169f11c84a5348197af75fe54f25acaf1\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp8RyxKMvekh9uf9kARA81O5yl0eh2OJR267wITHS74uR0ZhmDEHDRTyKgn0f0DEQSLmxrbkN4Lxq8I8wAlU5mu_fqt8vOkqiikYRpQJTn5L2r2Llc2ebBvrqvhSry-Jap64GPLzNdrJs2avA0PFTQWcVtBKzodc2g-HxarojOXgz6370-2nMALVIO8neQsiO0V41r4y2hLpSmNBBdW1NYbeHPxzy4n6otPATzrzPBrEBy2jsiECwQ-q9G4VyPCpp2rM2GgsnjnbiV1gK-dxY8Y7_WFbN-94eUkwYYwDVhz6_CtRqIAvHbhfSok4vJISAc3YBXGK6tYd49QYe9X37ojSH3n46YQrTEiewVehSLGistmkiD1_9ZzO-v0y3p0_W55qbhf0ccI3s1oG2sVovcy1QLeHQooaxPY_Gxet5nJVi8HFkKYvx_lzyJh2rPSJNGDNWyasPr7SBLAmlhEbG9eAOfb75CdYInMPGOPAQ_O1EKQIgL2QS5tLmA8d09b1mBBxSXpa