DynamicAccess records. I'm worried that direct reflection in tests might be disallowed, but accessing the public API from a child classloader could be a workaround due to testing classloader isolation. However, that feels risky. \\\\n\\\\nPerhaps a separate sourceSet and a JUnit test that forks a new Java process with a different classpath would be more straightforward. But, hmm, tests under a native image shouldn't spawn a Java process, right? That's not ideal.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing class usage**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether I need to include all primary classes. I see that the existing Hazelcast3's LocalMapStats and NearCacheStats are still relevant. The current tests are importing com.hazelcast.core.IMap and creating an old IMap proxy. However, I notice that the HazelcastIMapAdapter CLASS_I_MAP is now the primary fixture for com.hazelcast.map.IMap. I just need to figure out the best way to proceed with this setup!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_anMgAp6vDGj2JeYfYVcxh0aX|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11cb141e08197b76f847dae08376d\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git status --short && git log --oneline -3\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 46493, \"output\": 3092, \"cacheRead\": 4608, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 54193, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777409154122, \"responseId\": \"resp_07970394a73d0df90169f11c8361288197a191ea44a4c4bff2\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_anMgAp6vDGj2JeYfYVcxh0aX|fc_07970394a73d0df90169f11cb141e08197b76f847dae08376d\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"?? metadata/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/\\n8a2380566d (HEAD -> ai/add-lib-support-io.micrometer-micrometer-core-1.8.2) 